**Category:** essay-draft faith-reason aquinas aristotle practical-knowledge scholasticism

**Abstract:**
Research statement on faith and reason exploring the Aristotelian epistemological framework adopted by Aquinas. Argues that the scholastic conception of faith as intellectual assent to revealed doctrines derives from Aristotle's speculative epistemology. Proposes that divine revelation falls under practical knowledge (terminating in response) rather than speculative knowledge (terminating in assent).

**AI Recommendation:** Companion to 96-NOV-1-1 grant proposal; develops theological critique of scholastic rationalism.

